Just do it all in the condition instead of separately:<p><pre><code>    if ! command_that_may_error; then
        echo &quot;{\&quot;error\&quot;: \&quot;Failed to connect to the database.\&quot;}&quot; >&2;
        exit 1;
    fi</code></pre>

The problem with the `-e` flag is if you want to output custom errors, say json. I prefer to have bash inspect status codes.<p><pre><code>    if [ $? != 0 ]; then
        echo &quot;{\&quot;error\&quot;: \&quot;Failed to connect to the database.\&quot;}&quot; >&2;
        exit 1;
    fi</code></pre>
